## Multi-Run Experiments

### Seed Strategy for Multiple Runs

| Strategy | Implementation | Trade-off |
|----------|---------------|-----------|
| Sequential | Seeds: 0, 1, 2, ..., N-1 | Simple but correlated for small N |
| Hash-derived | `derive_seed(master, f"run_{i}")` | Independent, deterministic |
| Pre-generated | Fixed list in config file | Most transparent |

### Reporting Requirements

For experiments with multiple runs:

```yaml
experiment:
  master_seed: 42
  num_runs: 30
  seed_strategy: "hash_derived"
  seeds_used: [42, 1847293, 9182736, ...]  # or derivation formula
results:
  metric_mean: 0.847
  metric_std: 0.012
  metric_min: 0.821
  metric_max: 0.869
```

- [ ] Number of runs is justified (power analysis or convention)
- [ ] All seeds are recorded (not just the master seed)
- [ ] Mean, std, min, max, and median are reported
- [ ] Individual run results are available (not just aggregates)

