## Non-Determinism Documentation

### Known Sources of Non-Determinism

| Source | Controllable? | Mitigation |
|--------|--------------|------------|
| GPU atomicAdd (scatter, gather) | Partial | `torch.use_deterministic_algorithms(True)` |
| cuDNN autotuner | Yes | `cudnn.benchmark = False` |
| Multi-threaded data loading | Yes | `num_workers=0` or worker seeds |
| Hash table ordering (Python < 3.7) | Yes | `PYTHONHASHSEED` |
| Floating-point reduction order | Partial | Fixed reduction order, double precision |
| OS-level thread scheduling | No | Document, accept small variance |
| Network non-determinism (distributed) | Partial | Deterministic collectives |

### Tolerance Documentation

When perfect determinism is not achievable:

```yaml
reproducibility:
  deterministic: false
  tolerance:
    metric: "accuracy"
    max_deviation: 0.001  # 0.1%
    observed_deviation: 0.0003
  non_deterministic_sources:
    - "GPU atomicAdd in attention layer"
    - "cuBLAS workspace randomness"
  mitigation: "Results averaged over 30 runs"
```

